						<summary>

						<p>This mutilated inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 47, Plava, Jyēshṭha, śu. 2, Sunday, Dakshiṇāyana-saṁkramaṇa, vyatīpāta.</hi> The date is irregular. In Plava, Jyēshṭha śu. 2 did not fall on a Sunday; the Dakshiṇāyana-saṅkrānti, however, occurred on Sunday = 26th June A.D. 1121; but the tithi was Āshāḍha śu. 9. The record registers a grant of land made to a god (name lost). The Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Permāḍiyarasa Daṇḍanāyaka</hi> is mentioned. </p>						

						</summary>
